sentence: Home improvement warehouse operator The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) on Wednesday saw its price target cut by two separate brokerages.
Barclays Capital lowered its price target for HD to $35 from $37, citing mixed sales trends for the second quarter.
Still, that new target represents a healthy potential 24% upside to the stock's Tuesday closing price of $28.24.
Barclays also reiterated its "Overweight" rating on the stock.
Meanwhile, Jefferies & Co. lowered its earnings estimates for HD through 2012, citing lower housing demand.
The firm maintained its "Buy" rating, but cut its price target for the stock to $33.
We had removed shares of HD from our recommended list back on May 25, when the stock was trading at $33.22.
The company has a 3.33% dividend yield, based on last night's closing stock price of $28.24.
The stock has technical support in the $25 price area.
If the shares can firm up, we see overhead resistance around the $32 price levels.
We would remain on the sidelines for now.
